%20Shanta%20Gokhale%2C%20giving%20you%20an%20insight%20into%20the%20sometimes%20different%2C%20sometimes%20similar%20ways%20two%20translators%20may%20view%20the%20same%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20festival%2C%20Pinto%20spoke%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%20his%20work%20as%20a%20translator%2C%20why%20he%20thinks%20people%20need%20to%20expand%20their%20horizons%20in%20terms%20of%20how%20they%20read%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%E2%80%99ve%20translated%20a%20very%20wide%20range%20of%20things%20%E2%80%93%20poetry%2C%20fiction%2C%20memoirs.%20How%20do%20you%20choose%20the%20work%20you%20translate%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESee%2C%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20love%2C%20actually.%20I%20was%20the%20kind%20of%20child%20who%2C%20when%20he%20was%20growing%20up%2C%20or%20even%20as%20an%20adolescent%20or%20someone%20in%20college%2C%20if%20I%20read%20a%20book%20that%20I%20really%20liked%2C%20I%20would%20try%20and%20force%20it%20on%20other%20people.%20My%20first%20experience%20with%20that%20was%20with%C2%A0%3Cem%3EJohnny%20Got%20His%20Gun%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Dalton%20Trumbo.%20I%20just%20told%20everybody%2C%20%E2%80%98You%20should%20read%20this%20book.%E2%80%99%20But%20then%20it%20went%20up%20and%20down%20%E2%80%93%20my%20barometer%20was%20sometimes%20very%20off%2C%20like%20Jonathan%20Livingston%20Seagull%20turned%20me%20on%20tremendously%20at%20one%20point.%20I%20kept%20thinking%20it%20was%20liberational.%20Then%20some%20of%20the%20things%20I%20tried%20to%20force%20on%20people%20I%E2%80%99m%20still%20fond%20of%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EClockwork%20Orange%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0by%20Anthony%20Burgess%2C%20many%20things%20like%20that.%20And%20I%20always%20discovered%20that%20even%20when%20you%20did%20get%20someone%20to%20take%20the%20book%20from%20you%2C%20it%20ended%20up%20on%20a%20pile%20of%20books%20that%20they%20wanted%20to%20read%2C%20and%20about%20six%20months%20later%20they%E2%80%99d%20return%20it%20to%20you%2C%20or%20you%E2%80%99d%20claim%20it%20back.%20And%20they%20never%20did%20%5Bread%20it%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there%E2%80%99s%20still%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20that%20evangelical%20person%20stuck%20in%20my%20head%2C%20who%20feels%20if%20I%20read%20a%20book%20and%20really%20love%20it%2C%20other%20the%20people%20have%20the%20right%20to%20read%20it%20or%20should%20get%20to%20read%20it.%20It%20would%20be%20so%20wonderful%20if%20they%20would%20read%20it.%20Having%20said%20that%2C%20I%20would%20really%20love%20it%20if%20other%20people%20translated%20more%2C%20and%20I%20could%20just%20read%20the%20translations.%20Like%C2%A0Tejaswini%20Niranjana%20on%C2%A0Jayant%20Kaikini%20is%20such%20a%20good%20match%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20perfect%20a%20translator-author%20match.%20So%20I%E2%80%99m%20so%20grateful%20that%20there%20is%20a%C2%A0Tejaswini%20Niranjana%20doing%20Jayant%20Kaikini%E2%80%99s%20work.%20But%20in%20other%20cases%20I%20think%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20terrible%20shortage%20of%20translators.%20I%20hope%20that%20changes%20%E2%80%93%20I%E2%80%99m%20told%20that%20Ashoka%20%5BUniversity%5D%20for%20instance%20has%20a%20class%20in%20translation.%20And%20I%20think%20my%20publisher%20Speaking%20Tiger%20did%20actually%20publish%20one%20of%20the%20books%20that%20a%20young%20student%20in%20Ashoka%20translated.%20So%20I%E2%80%99m%20hopeful%20that%20in%2010-15%20years%2C%20there%20will%20be%20more%20translators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20said%20that%2C%20most%20translators%20get%20sucked%20into%20the%20money-making%20work%2C%20and%20the%20money%20is%20in%20non-fiction.%20And%20if%20not%20non-fiction%20then%20actually%20technical%20manuals%20and%20stuff%20like%20that%2C%20which%20is%20even%20more%20soul%20killing.%20Literature%20comes%20last%2C%20and%20poetry%20is%20last%20to%20the%20last.%20Because%20first%20it%E2%80%99s%20so%20difficult%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20almost%2C%20very%20close%20to%2C%20impossible.%20And%20second%20because%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20market%2C%20in%20any%20language%2C%20for%20poetry.%20Poetry%20requires%20subsidies%20of%20some%20kind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20the%20choice%20actually%20is%20not%20mine%2C%20the%20book%20makes%20the%20call%20and%20begins%20to%20live%20in%20your%20head%2C%20and%20you%20then%20you%20decide%20you%20must%20translate%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHas%20there%20been%20a%20book%20or%20author%20that%20you%20felt%20was%20your%20perfect%20match%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20like%20to%20think%20that%20they%E2%80%99ve%20all%20been%2C%20in%20that%20sense.%20When%20you%E2%80%99re%20translating%20someone%20you%20enter%20into%20a%20relationship%20with%20that%20work%20that%20is%20so%20intense%2C%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20almost%20like%20a%20love%20affair.%20But%20for%20me%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20kind%20of%20like%20cheating%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20wild%20affair%20that%20I%E2%80%99m%20having%20while%20I%E2%80%99m%20married%20to%20my%20own%20writing.%20I%20take%20these%20sneaky%20little%20breaks%20from%20what%20I%E2%80%99m%20working%20on%20to%20go%20and%20do%20a%20translation%2C%20and%20enjoy%20myself%20tremendously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20aspects%20of%20any%20work%20that%20have%20appealed%20to%20me.%20Like%20in%20Malika%20Amar%20Shaikh%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20the%20blistering%20honesty%20of%20%3Cem%3EMala%20Udhvasta%20Vhachay%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%93%20she%20confesses%20to%20cardinal%20sins%2C%20and%20with%20complete%20calmness.%20You%20feel%20when%20you%E2%80%99re%20reading%20it%20%E2%80%93%20how%20much%20your%20parents%20loved%20you%2C%20they%20made%20you%20so%20secure%20that%20you%20can%20say%20anything%20about%20yourself%20and%20know%20that%20it%20will%20be%20forgiven.%20Whoever%20her%20parents%20were%2C%20they%20did%20a%20great%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20say%20with%20something%20like%C2%A0%3Cem%3ECobalt%20Blue%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Efor%20instance%2C%20it%20was%20that%20peculiar%20silence%20that%20affects%20middle-class%20households%20about%20matters%20of%20sexuality%2C%20which%20I%E2%80%99ve%20always%20thought%20is%20why%20we%20have%20so%20many%20problems%20with%20child%20sexual%20abuse%20%E2%80%93%20because%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20not%20allowed%20to%20say%20anything%20about%20your%20genitals%20or%20about%20your%20sexuality%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20difficult%20to%20come%20home%20and%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98Uncle%20did%20that%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98Someone%20did%20this%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3Cem%3ECobalt%20Blue%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ehad%20a%20relatability%20which%20I%20thoroughly%20enjoyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMee%20Mithaachi%20Baahuli%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESalt%20Doll%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0book%2C%20was%20about%20Bombay%20in%20the%201940s%20and%20%E2%80%9950s.%20When%20I%20was%20a%20journalist%2C%20I%20had%20this%20great%20fixation%20with%20the%20Bombay%20dock%20explosion%20of%201944.%20The%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESS%20Fort%20Stikine%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Esails%20into%20town%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20carrying%20dynamite%2C%20cotton%2C%20gunpowder%20and%20gold%20bars%20to%20pay%20the%20soldiers%20in%20Bombay.%20Cotton%20has%20such%20a%20high%20internal%20heat%20that%20if%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20wet%20it%20continually%2C%20it%20catches%20fire%20on%20its%20own%20accord.%20So%20whoever%20was%20supposed%20to%20wet%20it%20went%20awol%2C%20probably%20went%20on%20a%20bender%2C%20the%20cotton%20caught%20fire%2C%20the%20dynamite%20exploded.%20The%20sound%20was%20so%20loud%20that%20the%20seismograph%20in%20Shimla%20recorded%20it.%20The%201%2C400%20tonnes%20of%20ship%20jumped%20in%20the%20air%20and%20fell%20across%20another%20ship.%20Lots%20of%20Colaba%20caught%20fire%2C%20it%20was%20a%20big%20moment%20in%20the%20history%20of%20tragedies.%20In%20%3Cem%3EBaluta%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Daya%20Pawar%E2%80%99s%20book%2C%20he%20records%20that%20moment%20and%20says%20my%20community%20started%20running%20towards%20the%20bomb%20site%2C%20because%20they%20knew%20wherever%20there%20was%20a%20bomb%20site%2C%20there%20would%20be%20salvageable%20stuff.%20And%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMee%20Mithaachi%20Baahuli%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Vandana%20Mishra%20is%20on%20stage%20as%20an%20actor%20and%20hears%20the%20sound%2C%20but%20must%20complete%20the%20performance.%20So%20it%20my%20city%20being%20woven%20in%20front%20of%20me%2C%20in%20the%20form%20of%20reminiscences.%20She%E2%80%99s%20very%20powerful%20and%20very%20exciting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20of%20course%20Swadesh%20Deepak%20I%20have%20always%20been%20fascinated%20by%2C%20for%20obvious%20reasons%20%E2%80%93%20accounts%20of%20psychological%20disturbance.%20But%20most%20of%20the%20reading%20I%20have%20done%20has%20been%20Western%3B%20here%20you%20may%20have%20stories%20or%20plays%20where%20one%20character%20has%20a%20mental%20problem%2C%20but%20they%E2%80%99re%20silent%20characters%20%E2%80%93%20they%20make%20an%20appearance%2C%20they%20disrupt%2C%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98rational%E2%80%99%20rest%20of%20the%20cast%20talks%20about%20them.%20There%20was%20a%20startling%20chain%20of%20coincidences%3A%20I%20started%20by%20doing%C2%A0%3Cem%3EEm%20and%20the%20Big%20Hoom%20%3C%2Fem%3E%5BPinto%E2%80%99s%20novel%20about%20a%20family%20in%20which%20the%20mother%20is%20struggling%20with%20bipolar%20disorder%5D.%20When%20I%20started%20doing%20conversations%2C%20readings%2C%20events%2C%20they%20turned%20into%20almost%20encounter%20groups%2C%20people%20telling%20stories%20of%20their%20encounters%20with%20mental%20health%20or%20family%20people%E2%80%99s%20encounters.%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20to%20deal%20with%20this%20kind%20of%20energy%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20a%20trained%20mental%20health%20professional.%20So%20I%20told%20a%20friend%2C%20and%20she%20said%20why%20don%E2%80%99t%20you%20tell%20them%20to%20write%20%E2%80%93%20it%20seems%20to%20have%20helped%20you.%20So%20I%20started%20doing%20that.%20Then%20one%20of%20them%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98If%20I%20write%20about%20it%2C%20then%20what%3F%E2%80%99%20Which%20is%20a%20good%20enough%20question%2C%20so%20%3Cem%3EA%20Book%20of%20Light%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ecame%20to%20be.%20It%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20neurodivergent%20people%20and%20carers%2C%20but%20the%20neurodivergent%20began%20to%20write%20in%20and%20say%20I%E2%80%99m%20being%20triggered%2C%20so%20my%20therapist%20said%20perhaps%20not.%20So%20I%20said%20okay%2C%20no%20book%20is%20worth%20a%20spell%20or%20anything%20like%20that.%20So%20I%20said%20to%20everyone%2C%20relax%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20worry%20about%20it%2C%20let%20it%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20went%20on%20to%20make%20it%20caregivers%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20last%20caregiver%20was%20Sukant%20Deepak%2C%20Swadesh%20Deepak%E2%80%99s%20son.%20In%20the%20course%20of%20that%20essay%2C%20he%20mentions%20%3Cem%3EMaine%20Mandu%20Nahin%20Dekha%3C%2Fem%3E.%20So%20I%20recorded%20that%20in%20my%20head%2C%20that%20I%20will%20buy%20this%20someday.%20But%20you%20just%20park%20it%2C%20and%20Bombay%20is%20not%20the%20best%20place%20to%20get%20Hindi%20books.%20And%20then%20I%20was%20clearing%20%5Bartist%5D%C2%A0Jehangir%20Sabavala%E2%80%99s%20archive%2C%20with%20his%20wife%20Shirin%2C%20and%20there%20was%20the%20book.%20I%20picked%20it%20up%20and%20was%20going%20to%20ask%20what%20it%20was%20doing%20there%2C%20when%20I%20realised%20myself%20%E2%80%93%20the%20cover%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMaine%20Mandu%20Nahin%20Dekha%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20a%20Jehangir%20Sabavala%20painting.%20He%20had%20asked%20permission%2C%20and%20sent%20a%20copy%20and%20signed%20it.%20So%20I%20asked%20Shirin%2C%20%E2%80%98Can%20I%20borrow%20this%3F%E2%80%99%20And%20she%20said%20sure.%20I%20started%20reading%20it%20on%20the%20bus%20home%3B%20I%20missed%20my%20stop.%20Which%20I%20have%20never%20done.%20I%20came%20back%2C%20and%20I%20was%20on%20Facebook%20at%20the%20time%2C%20and%20on%20Facebook%20I%20got%20in%20touch%20with%20Sukant%20Deepak%20and%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98You%20must%20translate%20this%20book.%E2%80%99%20And%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98It%E2%80%99s%20too%20personal%2C%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%20it.%E2%80%99%20I%20wrote%20back%2C%20%E2%80%98Then%20I%20will.%E2%80%99%20And%20he%20wrote%20back%2C%20%E2%80%98Delighted.%E2%80%99%20And%20I%20plunged%20into%20that.%20It%20was%20wild%2C%20because%20when%20Swadesh%20Deepak%20is%20really%20insane%2C%20he%20uses%20English%2C%20in%20the%20mental%20hospital.%20English%20is%2C%20he%20says%2C%20the%20language%20of%20liars%20and%20lies.%20But%20he%20loves%20English%20so%20much%20that%20he%E2%80%99s%20constantly%20quoting%20%5Bauthors%5D.%20Like%20W.B.%20Yeats%20visits%20him%20in%20the%20mental%20hospital%2C%20and%20speaks%20fluent%20Hindi.%20Yeats%20has%20learnt%20Hindi%20because%20he%20has%20got%20to%20speak%20to%20Muktibodh%2C%20who%20is%20also%20in%20the%20same%20heaven.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opening%20chapter%20is%20a%2030-page%20chapter%2C%20where%20Swadesh%20Deepak%20is%20making%20his%20re-entry%20into%20polite%20society%20after%20having%20been%20away%20for%20seven%20years%20of%20silence%2C%20insanity%20and%20trying%20to%20kill%20himself%20and%20burn%20himself%20alive.%20He%E2%80%99s%20made%20his%20re-entry%2C%20and%20for%2030%20pages%20he%20describes%20a%20conversation%20between%20Gagan%20Gill%2C%20Nirmal%20Verma%2C%20Vikas%20Rai%2C%20Krishna%20Sobti%20%E2%80%93%20all%20these%20people%20are%20sitting%20in%20a%20room%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20kind%20of%20thing%20I%E2%80%99ve%20always%20wanted%20to%20read.%20So%20it%20was%20just%20such%20a%20perfect%20book.%20He%E2%80%99s%20also%20a%20teacher%2C%20and%20obviously%20is%20a%20grandstanding%20teacher%20who%20always%20wore%20a%20coat%20and%20tie%2C%20and%20is%20very%20assured%20of%20his%20good%20looks.%20He%E2%80%99s%20terrifying%2C%20at%20some%20level.%20But%20in%20a%20distorted%20mirror%20I%20could%20see%20palely%20Jerry%20Pinto%2C%20teacher%E2%80%A6all%20of%20it.%20In%20some%20ways%20we%E2%80%99re%20always%20looking%20for%20that%20somewhat%20distorted%20reflection%20of%20ourselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20think%20it%20affects%20the%20process%2C%20or%20changes%20it%20dramatically%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20you%20can%20be%20in%20conversation%20with%20the%20author%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20few%20times%20that%20the%20author%20has%20been%20alive%20%E2%80%93%20I%E2%80%99m%20working%20on%20my%20first%20Konkani%20novel%20now%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20by%20Damodar%20Mauzo.%20I%20love%20the%20book%2C%20I%20admire%20deeply%20his%20courage%20to%20stand%20up%20against%20the%20Hindutva%20right%20wing%2C%20and%20to%20refuse%20to%20apologise%20for%20what%20he%20has%20said%2C%20which%20would%20have%20been%20the%20easy%20way%20out.%20I%20went%20and%20stayed%20with%20him%2C%20I%20asked%20him%20for%20a%20week%2C%20I%20said%20I%E2%80%99ll%20come%20to%20Goa%20and%20read%20my%20translation%20to%20you.%20He%20said%20okay%2C%20but%20instead%20of%20commuting%2C%20come%20and%20stay%20with%20me.%20So%20I%20went%20and%20stayed%20with%20him.%20It%20was%20lovely%2C%20every%20morning%20I%20would%20read%20his%20work%20to%20him%2C%20he%E2%80%99d%20be%20sitting%20with%20his%20Konkani%2C%20his%20wife%20was%20also%20a%20quiet%20presence%20in%20the%20corner%2C%20she%20has%20translated%20his%20book%20into%20Marathi.%20It%20was%20silky.%20I%E2%80%99m%20a%20very%20faithful%20translator%2C%20and%20where%20unfaithful%2C%20I%20run%20it%20by%20the%20author.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Sachin%20Kundalkar%20who%20was%20also%20alive%2C%20I%20read%20the%20whole%20book%20to%20him.%20The%20first%20two%20translations%20I%20did%20also%2C%20I%20read%20them%20to%20Shanta%20Gokhale.%20Fundamentally%20we%20live%20in%20a%20country%20which%20is%20ruthlessly%20communal.%20Nobody%20believes%20that%20Jerry%20Pinto%20should%20be%20translating%20from%20Marathi%20or%20Hindi.%20The%20first%20question%20at%20every%20reading%20I%20do%2C%20someone%20stands%20up%20and%20says%20do%20you%20know%20enough%20Marathi%20to%20translate.%20The%20first%20time%20I%20got%20asked%20this%20question%2C%20I%20got%20so%20angry%20that%20I%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98No%20I%20just%20pushed%20it%20into%20Google%20Translate%2C%20and%20pulled%20it%20out%20the%20other%20side%20and%20published%20it.%E2%80%99%20The%20second%20time%20I%20realised%20that%20if%20my%20name%20was%20Jaideep%20Pant%2C%20this%20would%20not%20have%20been%20a%20question.%20But%20I%20also%20realised%20that%20sometimes%20it%E2%80%99s%20coming%20from%20a%20good%20place%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20just%20that%20they%20haven%E2%80%99t%20parsed%20why%20they%E2%80%99re%20asking%20this%20question.%20So%20then%20I%20have%20an%20answer%2C%20I%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98English%20is%20my%20space%20of%20dreams%2C%20Marathi%20is%20my%20space%20of%20pilgrimage.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVery%20poetic.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYa%2C%20and%20everyone%20likes%20the%20poetic%20and%20the%20philosophical.%20A%20translator%20who%20shall%20go%20unnamed%20once%20said%20to%20me%2C%20%E2%80%98It%E2%80%99s%20better%20if%20they%E2%80%99re%20dead.%E2%80%99%20But%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20so.%20I%20really%20think%20if%20the%20person%20is%20alive%20and%20you%20can%20actually%20talk%20to%20them%20about%20what%20is%20the%20working%20of%20this%20book%2C%20you%20really%20get%20an%20insight%20into%20it%20that%20you%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20get%20otherwise.%20I%20have%20enjoyed%20conversations%20with%20the%20writers%20who%20are%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20want%20to%20go%20back%20to%20something%20you%20said%20right%20at%20the%20start%2C%20and%20this%20is%20no%20longer%20about%20translation%2C%20but%20about%20your%20inclination%20to%20push%20people%20to%20read%20the%20things%20that%20you%20like.%20I%20was%20reminded%20of%20something%20you%20said%20last%20year%20when%20you%20were%20speaking%20here.%20You%20were%20talking%20the%20importance%20of%20creating%20reading%20cultures%2C%20and%20how%20you%20feel%20there%20has%20been%20a%20loss%20over%20time.%20Do%20you%20believe%20this%20change%20has%20been%20significant%2C%20in%20reading%20cultures%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYes%20and%20no.%20No%20because%20of%20the%20sheer%20numbers%20seem%20to%20tell%20us%20that%20reading%20is%20rising.%20But%20I%20always%20say%20parse%20the%20numbers.%20Break%20them%20down.%20Are%20we%20talking%20Malayalam%20Manorama%3F%20Are%20we%20talking%20Competition%20Success%20Review%3F%20Are%20we%20talking%20self-help%2C%20are%20we%20talking%20cook%20books%2C%20if%20we%20are%2C%20then%20numbers%20are%20rising.%20And%20non-fiction.%20Literature%2C%20I%20think%2C%20has%20not%20risen%20significantly%20or%20in%20the%20same%20proportion%20that%20the%20others%20have.%20There%20was%20one%20year%20when%20everyone%20got%20excited%20because%20young%20adult%20reading%20had%20come%20of%20age%2C%20it%20was%20going%20to%20be%20the%20next%20big%20thing%2C%20everyone%20wanted%20a%20young%20adult%20list.%20I%20got%20at%20least%20three%20requests%20from%20very%20people%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%98Have%20you%20got%20a%20young%20adult%20book%3F%E2%80%99%20As%20though%20one%20keeps%20books%20in%20little%20corners.%20But%20eventually%20the%20young%20adult%20myth%20got%20blown%20out%20of%20the%20water%2C%20because%20that%20year%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Fault%20in%20Our%20Stars%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ehad%20come%20out.%20It%20was%20about%20two%20young%20kids%20who%20had%20sex.%20And%20then%20they%20both%20died%20of%20cancer.%20Young%20people%20just%20loved%20it%2C%20obviously.%20The%20big%20constraint%20was%20blown%20open.%20The%20next%20year%20there%20was%20no%20%3Cem%3EFault%20in%20Our%20Stars%3C%2Fem%3E.%20And%20young%20adult%20reading%20fell.%20It%E2%80%99s%20exactly%20like%3Cem%3E%C2%A0Harry%20Potter%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Because%20young%20people%20would%20come%20up%20to%20me%20and%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98Do%20you%20have%20any%20books%20like%20Harry%20Potter%3F%E2%80%99%20And%20I%20would%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98No%2C%20but%20there%20are%20many%20other%20books%20of%20many%20other%20types.%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98No%2C%20we%20want%20something%20like%20Harry%20Potter.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A6As%20adults%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20supposed%20to%20move%20on%20to%20the%20space%20where%20literature%20challenges%20you%2C%20and%20makes%20you%20uncomfortable%2C%20and%20makes%20you%20want%20to%20have%20different%20experiences.%20But%20somehow%20people%20just%20don%E2%80%99t%20grow%20past%20Harry%20Potter.%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20problem.%20So%20in%20that%20sense%20numbers%20have%20a%20certain%20value%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20accepting%20of%20that.%20But%20are%20we%20reading%20with%20curiosity%3F%20I%20wish%20people%20would%20read%20with%20the%20same%20enthusiasm%20that%20they%20experiment%20with%20new%20cuisines.%20So%20if%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20new%20Ethiopian%20restaurant%20in%20town%2C%20people%20will%20go%20and%20try%20it.%20But%20if%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20new%20book%20that%20has%20been%20translated%20from%20Dogri%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20same%20attitude.%20I%20think%20people%20who%20read%20in%20one%20language%2C%20not%20having%20decolonised%20their%20reading%20list%2C%20only%20read%20from%20say%20British%20writers%2C%20or%20American%20writers%2C%20are%20like%20a%20man%20who%20has%20a%20buffet%2C%20but%20eats%20chicken%20masala%20every%20day.%20Now%20the%20chicken%20masala%20is%20done%20very%20well%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20little%20different%20every%20day%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20exciting%20%E2%80%93%20but%20surely%20you%20should%20try%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20buffet%3F%20And%20with%20our%20generation%2C%20or%20your%20generation%20also%2C%20you%E2%80%99d%20read%20at%20least%20three%20scripts.%20But%20how%20many%20of%20those%20do%20you%20actually%20read%20in%2C%20in%20a%20year%3F%20So%20I%E2%80%99m%20saying%20spread%20out%2C%20buy%20a%20book%20of%20Bengali%2C%20in%20Hindi%3B%20don%E2%80%99t%20like%20it%2C%20pass%20it%20on%20to%20some%20hapless%20person%20as%20a%20birthday%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbout%2020%20years%20ago%20I%20decided%20to%20make%20it%20a%20sustained%20habit%2C%20that%20I%20would%20try%20and%20read%20every%20day%20in%20at%20least%20two%20of%20the%20three%20scripts%20I%20can%20read%20in.%20I%20feel%20that%20there%20are%20so%20many%20benefits%20of%20it%2C%20that%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20even%20need%20to%20say%20that%20your%20brain%20is%20getting%20sharper%2C%20your%20sense%20of%20language%20is%20getting%20more%20interesting.%20It%20just%20means%20that%20you%20are%20now%20listening%20into%20another%20world%2C%20as%20though%C2%A0%3Cem%3Edeewar%20gir%20gaya%20hai%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%20I%20can%20now%20listen%20to%20a%20Lucknowi%20place%2C%20or%20another%20one%20has%20fallen%20down%20and%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20Goan%20there%2C%20or%20there%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20Punjabi.%20It%E2%80%99s%20just%20such%20a%20wonderful%20thing%20to%20be%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20people%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98Oh%2C%20there%20are%20so%20few%20translations%20available%2C%E2%80%99%20quite%20frankly%20two%20things%20are%20in%20the%20way.%20One%20is%20that%20one%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20get%20paid%20very%20much%20for%20a%20translation.%20This%20I%20understand%2C%20because%20my%20publisher%20for%20instance%20is%20one%20of%20my%20best%20friends.%20He%20would%20give%20me%20money%20if%20he%20could%20give%20me%20money.%20And%20he%20can%E2%80%99t%20give%20me%20money%20because%20people%20will%20buy%20in%20those%20quantities.%20So%20the%20books%20will%20not%20sell%20like%20that.%20So%20it%20is%20fine.%20I%20feel%20that%20if%20we%20were%20just%20a%20little%20more%20experimental%20in%20our%20reading%2C%20we%20would%20all%20benefit.%20There%20would%20be%20more%20translations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20other%20problem%20is%20the%20way%20the%20media%20deals%20with%20it.%20It%E2%80%99s%20all%20about%20the%20pornography%20of%20money.%20So%20only%20if%20you%20have%20got%20a%20huge%20advance%2C%20in%20millions%20of%20dollars%2C%20will%20you%20make%20it%20to%20the%20news.%20Or%20you%20get%20a%20big%20prize.%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eof%20all%20places%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20had%20a%20headline%20which%20read%2C%20%E2%80%98Jerry%20Pinto%20Wins%20%24X%E2%80%99.%20I%20was%20horrified%20%E2%80%93%20this%20wa