lide%20to%20majoritarianism.%20It%20is%20time%20to%20reflect%20on%20the%20descent%20from%20secularism%20to%20a%20muscular%20Hinduism%20that%20casts%20a%20pall%20of%20fear%20over%20democratic%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20tragedy%20is%20that%20we%20came%20from%20a%20good%20place.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20May%201%2C%201947%2C%20Mahavir%20Tyagi%2C%20the%20Congress%20member%20from%20the%20United%20Provinces%2C%20suggested%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20that%20consideration%20of%20minority%20rights%20should%20be%20postponed.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20there%20is%20to%20be%20a%20partition%2C%20we%20must%20know%20what%20is%20happening%20to%20the%20minorities%20on%20the%20other%20side%2C%20in%20the%20other%20units%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20Dr.%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20replied%20resolutely%20that%20rights%20of%20minorities%20are%20absolute%20rights%2C%20they%20should%20not%20be%20held%20hostage%20to%20the%20policies%20of%20another%20country%20on%20its%20minorities.%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20that%20the%20rights%20which%20are%20indicated%20in%20clause%2018%20are%20rights%20which%20every%20minority%20irrespective%20of%20any%20other%20consideration%20is%20entitled%20to.%E2%80%9D%20This%20was%20the%20ethos%20that%20India%20began%20its%20postcolonial%20life%20with.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20should%20recollect%20that%20after%20the%20massive%20communal%20riot%20in%20Kanpur%20in%201931%2C%20the%20Congress%20drafted%20the%20Karachi%20Resolution%20on%20Fundamental%20Rights.%20The%20Declaration%20emphasised%20the%20right%20of%20every%20citizen%20to%20profess%2C%20and%20practice%20her%20religion.%20Later%20that%20year%2C%20on%20March%2031%2C%20Gandhi%2C%20moving%20the%20resolution%20on%20fundamental%20rights%20in%20the%20open%20session%20of%20the%20Congress%20in%20Karachi%2C%20spoke%20on%20the%20issue.%20Though%20Islamic%20and%20Aryan%20cultures%20are%20not%20mutually%20exclusive%20he%20said%2C%20we%20must%20recognise%20that%20Muslims%20look%20upon%20Islamic%20culture%20as%20distinctive%20from%20Aryan.%20Let%20us%20therefore%20cultivate%20tolerance.%20Religious%20neutrality%20is%20an%20important%20provision.%20Swaraj%20will%20favour%20Hinduism%20no%20more%20than%20Islam%2C%20nor%20Islam%20more%20than%20Hinduism.%20Let%20us%20from%20now%20on%2C%20he%20concluded%2C%20adopt%20the%20principle%20of%20state%20neutrality%20in%20our%20daily%20affairs.%20Gandhi%20knew%20that%20independence%20would%20bring%20formidable%20problems.%20These%20problems%20had%20to%20be%20resolved%20principally%2C%20not%20by%20the%20brute%20show%20of%20power.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fprotest-at-the-parliament-should-be-seen-as-fearlessness-not-terror%5C%22%3EProtest%20at%20the%20Parliament%20Should%20Be%20Seen%20as%20Fearlessness%2C%20Not%20Terror%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDemocratic%20India%20contributed%20to%20the%20making%20of%20an%20independent%20and%20secular%20India.%20A%20group%20of%20poets%2C%20who%20later%20coalesced%20into%20the%20Progressive%20Writers%20Association%20in%201936%2C%20wrote%20amazing%20lyrics%20to%20inspire%20the%20freedom%20struggle.%20Today%20the%20country%20is%20polarised%20between%20Hindi%20and%20Urdu.%20We%20forget%20that%20Maulana%20Hasrat%20Mohani%20(1875-1951)%20coined%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%98Inquilab%20Zindabad%E2%80%99.%20This%20became%20the%20rallying%20cry%20of%20the%20freedom%20struggle%3B%20the%20anthem%20of%20revolutionaries.%20He%20demanded%20%3Cem%3EAzaadi%20e%20Kaamil%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20complete%20independence%20in%201921%3A%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3ERasm%20e%20jafa%20kaamyab%20dekhiye%20kab%20tak%20rahe%3C%2Fem%3E%2F%3Cem%3EHubb%20e%20watan%20mast%20e%20khwab%20kab%20tak%20rahe%2FDaulat%20e%20Hindustan%20qabzah%20aghyar%20mein%2F%20Be%20adad%20O%20behisab%20dekhiye%20kab%20tak%20rahe%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Let%20us%20see%20how%20long%20we%20are%20oppressed%2C%20how%20long%20freedom%20remains%20but%20a%20dream%2C%20and%20how%20long%20the%20British%20plunder%20India%E2%80%99s%20riches).%20When%20Bhagat%20Singh%2C%20Raj%20Guru%2C%20and%20Sukhdev%20marched%20to%20the%20gallows%20they%20raised%20the%20slogan%20of%20Inquilab%20Zindabad.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20revolutionaries%20were%20inspired%20by%20Chandrashekar%20Azad%E2%80%99s%20(1906-1931)%20poem%3A%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EDushmanon%20ki%20goliyan%20ka%20hum%20samna%20karenge%2FAzad%20hi%20rahe%20hai%2C%20azaad%20hi%20rahenge%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3E(We%20will%20face%20the%20bullets%20of%20the%20enemy%2C%20we%20have%20been%20free%20and%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20free)%2C%20they%20were%20equally%20motivated%20by%20the%20poet%20of%20revolution%20Josh%20Malihabadi%20(1894-1982)%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Emera%20naara%2C%20inquilab%20o%20inquilab%20o%20inquilab%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20(my%20slogan%20is%20revolution).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHow%20do%20we%20differentiate%20between%20Hindu%20and%20Muslim%20poets%3F%20Both%20loved%20freedom%20and%20both%20wrote%20such%20amazing%20poetry%20to%20capture%20political%20resistance%20that%20in%20the%20process%20they%20transformed%20literature%20and%20poetry.%20Sajjad%20Zaheer%2C%20a%20progressive%20poet%2C%20wrote%20in%20his%20autobiography%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EReminiscences%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20%E2%80%98sensitive%20writers%20felt%20that%20they%20could%20not%20continue%20in%20the%20old%20mode%E2%80%A6It%20was%20no%20longer%20possible%20for%20the%20writers%20to%20continue%20to%20live%20in%20ivory%20towers%20and%20remain%20unconcerned%20with%20the%20lives%20and%20thoughts%20of%20common%20people.%E2%80%99%20He%20was%20referring%20to%20the%20wave%20of%20anti-fascism%2C%20socialism%20and%20radicalisation%20of%20culture%2C%20literature%20and%20poetry%2C%20or%20social%20realism%2C%20that%20swept%20India%20in%20the%201930s.%20Literary%20figures%20extended%20the%20goals%20of%20the%20freedom%20struggle%20to%20the%20fight%20against%20injustice%20and%20patriarchy%20within%20society.%20Witness%20the%20contrast%20between%20progressive%20writers%20and%20rabid%20Muslim%20and%20Hindu%20right-wingers%20who%20remain%20stuck%20in%20notions%20of%20%E2%80%98two%20nations%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07194357%2FIMG_2649.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22M20%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07194357%2FIMG_2649.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07194357%2FIMG_2649-300x120.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07194357%2FIMG_2649-1024x410.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671913%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBhisham%20and%20Balraj%20Sahni%2C%20Prithviraj%2C%20Raj%20and%20Shammi%20Kapoor%20and%20a%20number%20of%20stars%20including%20the%20debonair%20Dev%20Anand%2C%20as%20well%20poets-%20Jan%20Nisar%20Akhtar%2C%20Sahir%20Ludhianvi%2C%20and%20Sardar%20Jafri%20among%20others%2C%20spoke%20up%20and%20marched%20against%20communalism%2C%20poverty%20and%20social%20oppression%20in%201946%20in%20Bombay.%20The%20progressives%20taught%20us%20that%20society%20has%20to%20look%20outwards%20towards%20imperialism%2C%20but%20it%20also%20has%20to%20also%20look%20inwards%20and%20focus%20on%20the%20many%20contradictions%2C%20oppressions%2C%20and%20tyrannies%20of%20our%20own%20society.%20They%20radicalised%20the%20freedom%20struggle.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20first%20meeting%20of%20the%20PWA%2C%20Munshi%20Premchand%20gave%20the%20inaugural%20address%20in%20chaste%20Urdu.%20He%20told%20the%20audience%20that%20good%20literature%20can%20only%20be%20founded%20on%20truth%2C%20beauty%2C%20freedom%20and%20humanity.%20It%20has%20to%20reject%20all%20that%20inhibits%20human%20freedom%20and%20creativity%2C%20such%20as%20orthodoxy%20and%20obscurantism.%20%E2%80%98Literature%20is%20the%20outward%20form%20of%20the%20artist%E2%80%99s%20spiritual%20balance%2C%20and%20what%20harmony%20creates%20is%20never%20subversive.%20It%20nurtures%20in%20us%20the%20qualities%20of%20loyalty%2C%20sincerity%2C%20sympathy%2C%20justice%20and%20egalitarianism.%20Where%20these%20qualities%20exist%2C%20there%20is%20stability%20and%20life.%20Where%20they%20are%20wanting%2C%20there%20is%20division%2C%20selfishness%2C%20hatred%2C%20enmity%2C%20and%20death%E2%80%A6Literature%20makes%20our%20life%20natural%20and%20free%E2%80%A6it%20civilises%20the%20self.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20independence%2C%20India%20inherited%20a%20fractured%20land%20and%20a%20divided%20people.%20Partition%20was%20the%20cost%20the%20country%20paid%20for%20independence.%20A%20number%20of%20progressive%20poets%20voiced%20their%20opposition%20to%20Partition%2C%20but%20their%20hearts%20were%20heavy.%20History%2C%20after%20the%20first%20world%20war%2C%20had%20once%20again%20borne%20witness%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20nation%20had%20taken%20precedence%20over%20solidarity.%20Ahmad%20Faraz%2C%20a%20poet%20who%20had%20opted%20for%20Pakistan%2C%20wrote%20in%20despair%3A%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EAb%20kis%20ka%20jashn%20manaate%20ho%2FUs%20desh%20ka%20jo%20taqseem%20hua%2FUs%20desh%20ka%20geet%20sunaate%20ho%2FJo%20toot%20ke%20hi%20tasleem%20hua%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%5BWhat%20are%20you%20celebrating%2C%20a%20country%20which%20was%20divided%20to%20create%20Pakistan%3F%5D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpangs-of-unemployment-why-indias-youth-is-turning-to-bhagat-singh%5C%22%3EPangs%20of%20Unemployment%3A%20Why%20India%E2%80%99s%20Youth%20is%20Turning%20to%20Bhagat%20Singh%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPartition%20and%20independence%20were%20the%20twin%20faces%20of%20August%201947%20in%20India.%20The%20miracle%20is%20that%20a%20democratic%20constitution%20was%20written%20amidst%20the%20debris%20of%20destroyed%20homes%2C%20work%20places%20and%20places%20of%20worship.%20It%20was%20democratic%20despite%20massacres%20and%20frayed%20hopes%20that%20independence%20would%20herald%20a%20new%20era.%20The%20task%20the%20constitution%20makers%20had%20on%20their%20hands%20was%20a%20stupendous%20one.%20Indians%20spoke%20different%20languages%2C%20practiced%20distinctive%20rituals%2C%20possessed%20unique%20world%20views%2C%20and%20had%20diverse%20expectations%20of%20politics.%20A%20newly%20independent%20India%20strained%20at%20the%20seams%20with%20diversity%20and%20difference%2C%20both%20of%20which%20can%20prove%20troublesome%20categories.%20People%20were%20strangers%20to%20each%20other.%20And%20in%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20democracy%20was%20a%20stranger%20to%20them.%20Independence%20had%20come%20along%20with%20bloodshed%20and%20massacres%2C%20social%20hierarchies%20were%20left%20intact%2C%20elites%20continued%20to%20hold%20themselves%20above%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20people%2C%20and%20discrimination%20on%20grounds%20of%20religion%20and%20caste%20ran%20rife.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnce%20again%20progressive%20poets%2C%20realising%20their%20responsibility%20to%20create%20a%20harmonious%20India%2C%20wrote%20inspiring%20lyrics%20that%20transcended%20religious%20boundaries%20to%20focus%20on%20commonalities.%20In%201960%2C%20in%20the%20famous%20film%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBarsaat%20Ki%20Raat%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20directed%20by%20P.L%20Santoshi%2C%20Sahir%20Ludhianvi%20wrote%20the%20lyrics%20of%20a%20%3Cem%3Equawali%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98yeh%20ishq%20ishq%20hai%20ishq%20ishq%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20high%20point%20of%20the%20lyric%20were%20the%20lines%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EIshaq%20azaad%20hai%20Hindu%20na%20Musalman%20hai%20Ishq%2F%20aap%20hi%20dharam%20hai%20and%20aap%20hi%20imaan%20hai%20Ishq%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Love%20is%20free%2C%20neither%20Hindu%20nor%20Muslim%2C%20it%20is%20in%20itself%20dharma%20and%20belief).%20And%20for%20a%201961%20film%2C%20B.R%20Chopra%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDharamputr%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%2C%20Sahir%20wrote%3A%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EKaabe%20mein%20rahon%20ya%20kashi%20mein%2C%20nisbat%20to%20usiki%20baat%20se%20hai%2C%20tum%20ram%20kaho%2C%20yah%20Rahim%20kaho%2C%20maqsad%20to%20usiki%20zaat%20se%20hai%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Whether%20you%20live%20in%20Kaaba%20or%20Kashi%20you%20are%20concerned%20with%20one%20God%2C%20whether%20you%20call%20him%20Ram%20or%20Rahim).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhere%20does%20Bollywood%20stand%20today%20on%20majoritarianism%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F14140600%2F142282.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F14140600%2F142282.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F14140600%2F142282-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F14140600%2F142282-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-330200%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20Instagram%2Fkaranjohar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20constitution%20as%20a%20social%20contract%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20constitution%20is%20a%20social%20contract%20that%20establishes%20a%20relationship%20between%20citizens%20and%20the%20state.%20It%20also%20establishes%20a%20relationship%20between%20citizens.%20A%20people%20who%20had%20been%20divided%20along%20the%20lines%20of%20politicised%20religion%20had%20to%20accept%20each%20other%20as%20members%20of%20a%20democratic%20political%20community%20constituted%20by%20the%20constitution.%20They%20were%20given%20an%20alternative%20to%20living%20in%20claustrophobic%20caste%20or%20religious%20communities%2C%20to%20know%20what%20cosmopolitanism%2C%20solidarity%20and%20friendship%20meant.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20was%20introduced%20to%20new%20norms%20enshrined%20in%20the%20preamble%20of%20the%20constitution%20and%2C%20above%20all%2C%20to%20the%20recognition%20of%20the%20importance%20of%20%E2%80%98we%20the%20people%E2%80%99%20i.e.%20popular%20sovereignty.%20We%20now%20owed%20obligations%20not%20only%20to%20the%20people%20we%20had%20elected%20into%20power%2C%20but%20also%20obligations%20to%20each%20other%20as%20fellow%20citizens.%20Thus%2C%20a%20political%20community%20based%20on%20fidelity%20to%20the%20constitution%20was%20born%20which%2C%20despite%20a%20rocky%20biography%20in%20the%20years%20since%20independence%2C%20has%20been%20consolidated%20through%20political%20action%20and%20through%20the%20development%20of%20solidarity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20foundations%20of%20this%20community%20had%20been%20laid%20during%20the%20freedom%20struggle%20by%20leaders%2C%20cadres%2C%20literature%20and%20progressive%20writers%20and%20poets.%20Poet%20Brij%20Narain%20Chakbast%20(1882-1926)%20spoke%20of%20the%20ability%20of%20a%20subject%20people%20to%20rise%20in%20unity%20against%20the%20power%20of%20the%20colonial%20state%3A%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EYeh%20Khaak%20e%20Hind%20se%20paide%20hain%20josh%20ke%20aasar%2FHimalaya%20se%20uthe%20jaise%20abr-e-daryabaar.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20coming%20together%20of%20people%20in%20a%20massive%20struggle%20for%20independence%20could%20have%20proved%20fragile%2C%20if%20a%20democratic%20constitution%20had%20not%20built%20on%20the%20anti-colonial%20project%20to%20create%20a%20project%20of%20solidarity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F676925%2Fthe-opium-of-nationalism%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Opium%20of%20Nationalism%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESolidarity%20is%20built%20upon%20civic%20mindedness%2C%20and%20good%20will%20towards%20fellow%20citizens.%20Democratic%20institutions%20will%20collapse%20if%20these%20two%20attributes%20are%20overtaken%20by%20racial%20and%20religious%20intolerance.%20Democracy%20is%20not%20only%20dependent%20on%20institutions%2C%20it%20is%20dependent%20on%20the%20relationship%20between%20citizens.%20And%20whether%20they%20see%20the%20political%20community%20as%20not%20only%20meant%20for%20the%20majority%20group%20but%20also%20their%20willingness%20to%20accept%20others%20as%20equals%20and%20as%20worthy%20of%20civil%20behaviour.%20Any%20deviation%20from%20or%20violation%20of%20these%20norms%20harm%20democracy%20and%20secularism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20Congress%20leaders%20used%20the%20term%20secularism%20in%20the%20pre-independence%20period%20often%2C%20oddly%20enough%20the%20concept%20was%20never%20spelt%20out%20or%20elaborated%20as%20a%20principle%20of%20state%20policy%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly.%20Nor%20was%20it%20included%20in%20the%20preamble%20until%201976%2C%20vide%20the%2042nd%20Amendment.%20Yet%2C%20commitment%20to%20secularism%20was%20visible%20throughout%20the%20debates%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20instance%2C%20most%20members%20agreed%20that%20the%20preamble%20should%20not%20contain%20any%20reference%20to%20God.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20October%2017%2C%201949%2C%20during%20discussions%20on%20the%20wording%20of%20the%20preamble%2C%20H.V.%20Kamath%20moved%20an%20amendment%20that%20it%20should%20begin%20with%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%98In%20the%20name%20of%20God%E2%80%99.%20Similar%20amendments%20were%20moved%20by%20Shibban%20Lal%20Saxena%20and%20Pandit%20Mohan%20Malviya.%20Other%20members%20objected%2C%20and%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20members%20expressed%20their%20conviction%20that%20religion%20was%20a%20matter%20of%20individual%20choice%20and%20not%20the%20signpost%20of%20a%20collective.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F06100716%2FIMG_6848.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F06100716%2FIMG_6848.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F06100716%2FIMG_6848-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F06100716%2FIMG_6848-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-661861%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPandit%20Hriday%20Nath%20Kunzru%20regretfully%20stated%20that%20a%20matter%20concerning%20our%20innermost%20and%20sacred%20feelings%20have%20been%20brought%20into%20the%20arena%20of%20discussion.%20It%20would%20have%20been%20far%20more%20consistent%20with%20our%20beliefs%20that%20we%20should%20not%20impose%20our%20feelings%20on%20others%2C%20and%20that%20the%20collective%20view%20should%20not%20have%20been%20forced%20on%20others.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20invoke%20the%20name%20of%C2%A0%20God%2C%20but%20I%20make%20bold%20to%20say%20that%20while%20we%20do%20so%2C%20we%20are%20showing%20a%20narrow%20sectarian%20spirit%2C%20which%20is%20contrary%20to%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20Constitution.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20amendment%20moved%20by%20Mr%20Kamath%20was%20defeated.%20Members%20stressed%20on%20the%20need%20to%20curtail%20religion%20in%20the%20public%20sphere%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20nation%20building%2C%20of%20democracy%20and%20of%20rights.%20On%20November%2023%2C%201948%2C%20K.M%20Munshi%20emphasised%20that%20religion%20must%20be%20restricted%20to%20spheres%20which%20legitimately%20appertain%20to%20religion.%20The%20rest%20of%20life%20must%20be%20regulated%2C%20unified%20and%20modified%20in%20order%20to%20build%20a%20strong%20and%20consolidated%20nation.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20December%202%2C%201948%2C%20Dr%20Ambedkar%20asked%20for%20strict%20control%20over%20religion.%20Religious%20conceptions%20in%20this%20country%2C%20he%20said%2C%20are%20so%20vast%20that%20they%20cover%20every%20aspect%20of%20life%20from%20birth%20to%20death.%20We%20should%20strive%20to%20limit%20the%20definition%20of%20religion%20so%20that%20it%20does%20not%20extend%20beyond%20beliefs%20and%20rituals%20of%20ceremonies.%20In%20sum%2C%20the%20role%20of%20religion%20in%20public%20affairs%20was%20sought%20to%20be%20depoliticised%2C%20and%20religion%20privatised%2C%20so%20that%20the%20public%20sphere%20and%20state%20policy%20could%20be%20governed%20by%20secular%20or%20non-religious%20politics.%20This%20was%20the%20constitution%20that%20the%20people%20of%20India%20gave%20to%20themselves%20%E2%80%93%20a%20product%20of%20mass%20struggle%2C%20political%20compromises%2C%20idealism%20and%20commitment%20to%20every%20citizen.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20adoption%20of%20a%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20whose%20preamble%20majorly%20reflected%20the%20demands%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement%20%E2%80%93%20realised%20dreams%20and%20longings%20that%20had%20been%20stirred%20by%20poetry%2C%20fiery%20speeches%20of%20revolution%2C%20political%20protests%20and%20by%20the%20selfless%20devotion%20of%20outstanding%20men%20and%20women%20to%20the%20country.%20The%20day%20the%20constitution%20was%20promulgated%20on%20January%2026%2C%201950%2C%20was%20a%20day%20of%20great%20joy%20and%20fulfilment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20perhaps%2C%20the%20constitution%20began%20to%20be%20taken%2C%20by%20succeeding%20generations%2C%20for%20granted%20except%20as%20a%20document%20that%20has%20been%20interpreted%20and%20reinterpreted%20by%20the%20courts.%20I%20wonder%20how%20many%20Indians%20recognise%20that%20the%20constitution%20is%20also%20political%20document.%20The%20preamble%20embodies%20the%20ideals%20of%20a%20generation%20that%20fought%20for%20independence%20for%20generations%20that%20were%20to%20follow.%20What%20else%20were%20people%20fighting%20for%20if%20they%20were%20not%20fighting%20against%20the%20might%20of%20the%20colonial%20power%20for%20independence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToday%2C%20we%20should%20re-discover%20that%20moment%20of%20excitement%20and%20joy%20when%20India%20got%20her%20own%20constitution.%20We%20need%20to%20rediscover%20that%20sense%20of%20pride%20that%20our%20constitution%20has%20been%20fought%20for%20by%20millions%20of%20people%2C%20for%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20constitution%20which%20embodied%20the%20commitment%20of%20the%20national%20movement%20is%20considered%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20finest%20in%20the%20world.%20There%20is%20nothing%20a%20people%20cannot%20do%20when%20they%20come%20together%20in%20a%20community%20that%20transcends%20caste%2C%20regional%20and%20religious%20affiliations.%20A%20people%20who%20unite%20in%20the%20associational%20space%20of%20the%20political%20community%20have%20great%20power.%20That%20is%20why%20so-called%20leaders%2C%20and%20political%20parties%20aspiring%20to%20power%2C%20try%20to%20divide%20people%20along%20the%20lines%20of%20religious%20affiliation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20the%20political%20community%2C%20relatively%20autonomous%20of%20the%20rites%20of%20procedural%20politics%2C%20and%20characterised%20by%20deliberation%20and%20dialogue%20reiterates%20a%20truth%20that%20is%20often%20overlooked%20by%20legal%20jurists.%20A%20society%20cannot%20be%20held%20together%20only%20by%20the%20dry%20bones%20of%20law.%20Unless%20people%20relate%20to%20each%20other%20with%20sympathy%20because%20they%20are%20fellow%20citizens%2C%20and%20who%20inhabit%20a%20community%20of%20fate%2C%20legal%20ties%20can%20prove%20brittle%2C%20laws%20can%20be%20subverted%2C%20corrupted%20and%20ignored.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPolitical%20communities%20should%20be%20able%20to%20reach%20out%20and%20connect%20with%20each%20other%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20poetic%20sympathy%20and%20solidarity.%20Otherwise%2C%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20live%20in%20the%20Hobbesian%20pre-political%20state%20of%20potential%20war%20against%20others.%20And%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20ask%20ourselves%2C%20did%20not%20we%20not%20learn%20anything%20from%20history%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fneera-chandhoke%5C%22%3ENeera%20Chandhoke%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20Delhi%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705240906000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F20123532%2FIMG_2186.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwe-the-people-a-call-to-remember-what-the-indian-constitution-stands-for%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20constitution%20that%20the%20people%20of%20India%20gave%20to%20themselves%20was%20a%20product%20of%20mass%20struggle%2C%20political%20compromises%2C%20idealism%20and%20commitment%20to%20every%20citizen.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwe-the-people-a-call-to-remember-what-the-indian-constitution-stands-for%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Not%20My%20Temple%3A%20A%20Personal%20Note%20on%20God%2C%20Places%20of%20Worship%20and%20the%20Law%20Governing%20These%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14191654%2FGC1E3sZWUAAAUI-.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Ram%20mandir%20is%20set%20to%20be%20consecrated%20amid%20much%20fanfare%20on%20January%2022%2C%202024.%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20alongside%20a%20host%20of%20other%20celebrities%20such%20as%20athletes%2C%20film%20stars%2C%20industrialists%2C%20and%20spiritual%20leaders%2C%20are%20set%20to%20grace%20the%20grand%20celebration%20in%20Ayodhya.%20The%20noise%20in%20anticipation%20of%20the%20occasion%20has%20been%20loud%2C%20intense%20and%20unyielding%2C%20not%20only%20in%20recent%20times%20but%20since%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%201992%2C%20and%20perhaps%20even%20earlier%20for%20others.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20people%20of%20the%20Hindu%20faith%20across%20the%20world%2C%20I%20am%20sure%2C%20are%20overjoyed%2C%20ecstatic%2C%20even%20fulfilled.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%2C%20in%20stark%20contrast%2C%20am%20filled%20with%20anxiety%2C%20pain%2C%20fear%2C%20sadness%2C%20betrayal%2C%20helplessness%2C%20and%20regret.%20The%20external%20clamor%20mirrors%20an%20internal%20disquiet%2C%20a%20constant%2C%20thumping%20noise%20in%20my%20head%20that%20I%20now%20recognise%20as%20my%20heart%20racing%20to%20match%20the%20pace%20of%20my%20anxiety.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%2011%20years%20old%20when%20a%20mosque%20from%20the%2016%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20century%20was%20violently%20demolished.%20As%20riots%20ravaged%20the%20city%20of%20Lucknow%20(close%20to%20Ayodhya%20where%20the%20mosque%20was%20located)%2C%20I%20spent%20a%20sleepless%20night%20with%20a%20knife%20under%20my%20pillow%20in%20case%20the%20mobs%20reached%20our%20doorsteps.%20I%20could%20hear%20the%20rioting%20but%20was%20thankfully%20spared%20from%20witnessing%20it.%20I%20woke%20up%20the%20next%20day%20to%20see%20the%20Times%20of%20India%20carrying%20a%20picture%20of%20%3Cem%3Ekar%20sevaks%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20the%20dome%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20with%20the%20headline%2C%20%E2%80%9CKarsevaks%20Destroyed%20Babri%20Masjid.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20day%20was%20eerily%20silent%20due%20to%20an%20imposed%20curfew%2C%20but%20the%20noise%20in%20my%20head%20persisted.%20I%20recall%20the%20day%20less%20for%20its%20events%20and%20more%20for%20the%20overwhelming%20emotions%20it%20left%20behind%20%E2%80%93%20anxiety%2C%20pain%2C%20fear%2C%20sadness%2C%20betrayal%2C%20helplessness%2C%20and%20regret.%20The%20feelings%20that%20I%20have%20carried%20well%20into%20my%20adult%20life%2C%20that%20have%20complicated%20my%20relationship%20with%20god%2C%20and%20faith%20itself.%20Overnight%2C%20my%20god%2C%20who%20is%20benevolent%2C%20and%20kind%2C%20with%20soft%20lotus%20like%20eyes%2C%20was%20transformed%20into%20an%20angry%20warrior%20king%2C%20an%20unrecognisable%20political%20force.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20temple%20has%20been%20a%20big%20victory%20for%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party.%20They%20stuck%20to%20their%20ideology%20and%20delivered%20on%20a%20promise%20to%20their%20followers.%20After%20decades%20of%20mobilisation%2C%20the%20grand%20opening%20of%20the%20temple%20is%20now%20the%20ultimate%20prize.%20And%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20hurt%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20so%20close%20to%20the%20general%20election%20coming%20up%20in%20less%20than%20six%20months.%20The%20temple%20is%20however%20just%20a%20representation%20of%20the%20complete%20suppression%20of%20anyone%20and%20everyone%20that%20believed%20India%20to%20be%20a%20diverse%2C%20multicultural%20society%20with%20a%20well-functioning%20constitutional%20democracy.%C2%A0%20It%20also%20shows%20that%20not%20only%20is%20the%20BJP%20dominating%20politics%2C%20society%2C%20and%20culture%20but%20also%20controlling%20other%20constitutional%20bodies.%20A%20situation%20I%20could%20not%20have%20foreseen%20when%20I%20was%20studying%20law%20at%20Delhi%20University%20in%20the%20early%202000s.%20A%20feeling%20of%20disillusionment%20with%20politics%20had%20started%20to%20take%20hold%2C%20especially%20after%20the%20Gujarat%20riots%20in%202002%2C%20but%20a%20deep%20faith%20in%20law%20and%20its%20guardian%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%E2%80%93%20had%20existed.%20That%20faith%20was%20shaken%20when%20the%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fayodhya-verdict-supreme-court-judgment%5C%22%3Edelivered%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20decision%20in%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20scholars%20have%20written%20about%20the%20case%20and%20analysed%20the%20various%20facets%20of%20the%20law%20of%20possession%2C%20religious%20worship%2C%20limitation%2C%20and%20inherent%20powers%20of%20Article%20142%20of%20the%20constitution%20of%20India.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20congratulated%20for%20ending%20a%20decades%20long%20problem.%20An%20act%20of%20great%20statesmanship%2C%20the%20only%20possible%20solution%20to%20a%20knotty%20land%20dispute.%20And%20to%20me%20that%E2%80%99s%20where%20the%20problem%20lies.%20To%20reduce%20a%20monumental%20issue%20that%20led%20to%20the%20complete%20breakdown%20of%20law%20and%20launched%20the%20country%20into%20a%20crisis%20of%20faith%20to%20a%20land%20dispute%20is%20an%20extremely%20problematic%20framing.%20The%20court%20itself%20admitted%20that%20it%20was%20called%20on%20to%20determine%20the%20legal%20consequences%20arising%20out%20of%20a%20thousand%20years%20of%20prayer%2C%20contest%2C%20construction%2C%20and%20destruction%20at%20the%20disputed%20site.%20It%20was%20never%20%E2%80%98just%E2%80%99%20a%20dispute%20over%20land%2C%20or%20title%20or%20possession%20but%20one%20about%20doing%20justice%20and%20fairness%20qua%20not%20only%20a%20minority%20community%20but%20also%20people%20like%20me%2C%20who%20believe%20that%20India%20is%20secular%2C%20that%20the%20rights%20of%20minorities%20are%20protected%2C%20that%20might%20is%20not%20right%2C%20and%20Hinduism%20is%20an%20inclusive%20and%20empathetic%20religion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-mathura-varanasi-why-the-coming-week-is-crucial-for-the-hindutva-project%5C%22%3EAyodhya%2C%20Mathura%2C%20Varanasi%3A%20Why%20the%20Coming%20Week%20Is%20Crucial%20for%20the%20Hindutva%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20had%20concluded%20that%20the%20Hindus%20established%20a%20clear%20case%20of%20possessory%20title%20ostensibly%20on%20the%20principles%20of%20justice%2C%20equity%20and%20good%20conscience%2C%20but%20the%20decision%20shows%20that%20the%20verdict%20went%20in%20their%20favour%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20belief%2C%20faith%20and%20the%20ostensible%20existence%20of%20continued%20worship%20(longer%20than%20the%20Muslim%20community%E2%80%99s).%20Despite%20whatever%20the%20court%20would%20like%20us%20to%20believe%2C%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20more%20moved%20by%20the%20unshakable%20faith%20of%20the%20Hindu%20community%20undeterred%20in%20the%20face%20of%20an%20Islamic%20Mosque%2C%20that%20Lord%20Ram%20was%20born%20at%20the%20disputed%20site%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20encroachment%20and%20destruction%20of%20a%20Muslim%20religious%20site%2C%20it%20becomes%20challenging%20to%20receive%20the%20court%20as%20guardians%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20minorities%20or%20its%20renowned%20multicultural%20heritage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJustice%20Kaul%2C%20recently%20in%20the%20decision%20on%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20recommended%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20as%20a%20trust%20building%20mechanism.%20But%20how%20is%20one%20to%20build%20trust%20when%20the%20building%20blocks%20of%20accountability%2C%20respect%2C%20and%20empathy%20are%20missing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDr.%20Rajeev%20Dhavan%20argued%20that%20the%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20case%20centred%20around%20%E2%80%9Cjustice%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20good%20conscience.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20applying%20these%20principles%2C%20claimed%20to%20achieve%20the%20%E2%80%9Cultimate%20balance%20for%20a%20just%20society%E2%80%9D%20by%20ruling%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20prevailing%20party.%20The%20notions%20of%20right%20and%20wrong%20are%20typically%20clear-cut%3B%20even%20a%20five-year-old%20understands%20not%20to%20harm%20a%20neighbour%E2%80%99s%20possessions.%20By%20typing%20up%20the%20issue%20in%20complicated%20legal%20knots%2C%20the%20court%20failed%20us%20by%20ignoring%20the%20interests%20of%20justice.%20The%20Ayodhya%20decision%20was%20unjust%2C%20and%20the%20imminent%20inauguration%20of%20the%20temple%20is%20morally%20objectionable.%20Instead%20of%20embodying%20the%20tenets%20of%20Hinduism%20like%20%3Cem%3Eahimsa%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20peace%2C%20non-violence%2C%20and%20harmony%2C%20the%20Ram%20temple%20stands%20for%20violence%20and%20has%20been%20reduced%20to%20a%20symbol%20of%20a%20majoritarian%20state.%20It%20delivers%20a%20very%20disconcerting%20message%20to%20the%20world-%20you%20can%20get%20what%20want%20by%20ugly%2C%20brutal%20force.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%2011-year-old%20me%20is%20as%20disillusioned%20as%20the%2042-year-old%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDevyani%20Kacker%20is%20a%20lawyer%20working%20in%20the%20human%20rights%20and%20the%20non-profit%20space.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705240178000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14191654%2FGC1E3sZWUAAAUI-.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fnot-my-temple-a-personal-note-on-god-places-of-worship-and-the-law-governing-these%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Ayodhya%20decision%20was%20unjust%2C%20and%20the%20imminent%20inauguration%20of%20the%20temple%20is%20morally%20objectionable.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fnot-my-temple-a-personal-note-on-god-places-of-worship-and-the-law-governing-these%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22CredAble%20records%20a%20two-fold%20increase%20in%20loan%20disbursements%20in%202023%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705237631000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-10%2F08%2Ffull%2F1696782663-0902.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fstart-ups%2Fcredable-records-a-two-fold-increase-in-loan-disbursements-in-2023-124011400402_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20company%20plans%20to%20raise%20%2450-75%20million%20by%20June%20this%20year%20in%20its%20series%20C%20round%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fstart-ups%2Fcredable-records-a-two-fold-increase-in-loan-disbursements-in-2023-124011400402_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fstart-ups%2Fcredable-records-a-two-fold-increase-in-loan-disbursements-in-2023-124011400402_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fstart-ups%2Fcredable-records-a-two-fold-increase-in-loan-disbursements-in-2023-124011400402_1.ht