20thick%20the%20dust%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Eknow%20them%20as%20before.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EOld%20Words%20for%20Old%20Things%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20best%20to%20use%20old%20words%20for%20old%20things.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EGoggles%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20better%20than%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eshades%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20words%20hustle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20smell%20of%20houses%20painted%20over%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20no%20trace%20of%20soul.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20words%20pay%20no%20mind%20to%20anything.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20are%20full%20of%20bluster%2C%20whereas%20old%20words%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Eold%20words%20are%20quiet.%20They%20tunnel%20through%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Eclimb%20ladders%20%E2%80%93%20a%20step%20at%20a%20time%20%E2%80%93%20on%20bad%20knees.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOld%20words%20are%20tortoises.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETake%20it%20from%20me%2C%20they%20get%20there%20in%20the%20end.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0K.%20Srilata%20is%20a%20poet%2C%20fiction%20writer%2C%20translator%20and%20academic.%20Srilata%E2%80%99s%20books%20include%20This%20Kind%20of%20Child%3A%20A%20%E2%80%98Disability%E2%80%99%20Story%20(Westland)%2C%20a%20novel%20Table%20for%20Four%20(Penguin%2C%20India)%20which%20was%20long%20listed%20in%202009%20for%20the%20Man%20Asian%20literary%20prize%2C%20six%20collections%20of%20poetry%20and%20the%20anthologies%20The%20Rapids%20of%20a%20Great%20River%3A%20The%20Penguin%20Book%20of%20Tamil%20Poetry%20and%20Short%20Fiction%20from%20South%20India%20(OUP).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2F